title.narrative: Strengthened child protection legal, policy and regulatory frameworks

description.narrative: Child protection legal, policy and regulatory frameworks were strengthened with progress in implementing the recommendations in the child protection mapping review, assessment and action plan for both Gaza and the West Bank. Four UNICEF supported CP Counsellors reached 439 complex statutory cases in the West Bank. The development of mediation guidelines has strengthened an inter-sectoral restorative justice approach for children in conflict with the law. The CP AoR has facilitated coordinated child protection service provision to 32,018 children (15,637 girls and 16,381 boys). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2020
